article.description: Spencer Parker scored 22 points on 8-of-15 shooting and Bowling Green rallied to beat Ohio 91-75 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Bowling Green rallies to beat Ohio 91-75
article.linkText: Bowling Green rallies to beat Ohio 91-75
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- Spencer Parker scored 22 points on 8-of-15 shooting and Bowling Green rallied to beat Ohio 91-75 Tuesday night. Ismail Ali scored 19 points, Rasheed Worrell added 13, and Antwon Lillard and Zach Denny scored 12 apiece for the Falcons (11-5, 2-1 Mid-American Conference), who made 22 of 30 free throws. Trailing by five at halftime, Bowling Green rallied to lead 51-46 after a 14-3 run in which Parker scored eight points. Ohio closed to within 60-56 with 10:48 left on a 3-pointer by Jordan Dartis, but Bowling Green pulled away on a 9-4 spurt in which Parker hit a layup and 3-pointer. Ali made five free throws in the final 2:49 and the Falcons outscored the Bobcats 9-6 down the stretch. Bowling Green won the rebound battle 42-32 and the Bobcats were hurt by 30 personal fouls. Kenny Kaminski scored 15 points, Antonio Campbell and Jaaron Simmons added 13 each, and Dartis had 11 for the Bobcats (10-5, 1-2).
